US President Donald Trump has taken to Twitter to accuse China and Europe of “playing big currency manipulation game and pumping money into their system in order to compete with USA”, According to Sputniknews.com. The remarks came a day after Trump stated that a trade deal between Washington and Beijing is already in the works and that negotiations are underway via phone. This preceded Trump and his Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping meeting on 27 June on the sidelines of the Osaka G20 summit and agreeing to resume trade talks, which had been paused since a breakdown in May.